{"id": 223691232, "title": "Police: Pedestrian struck in Bridgeport; driver stays at scene", "text": "A pedestrian was struck by a vehicle while walking in Bridgeport on Saturday evening, police said. Officers responded to the intersection of Fairfield Avenue and Clinton Avenue, where the pedestrian had been hit, about 6:45 p.m. according to the Bridgeport Police Department. The pedestrian, who has not been identified, was taken to a nearby hospital for treatment for their injuries, police said. The person who hit them stayed at the scene and an investigation was ongoing.", "summary": "Police: Pedestrian struck in Bridgeport", "url": "https://www.courant.com/2024/05/26/police-pedestrian-struck-in-bridgeport-driver-stays-at-scene/", "image": "https://www.courant.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/hartfall.jpg", "video": null, "publish_date": "2024-05-26 13:08:08", "author": "Taylor Hartz", "authors": ["Taylor Hartz"], "language": "en", "source_country": "US", "sentiment": -0.582}